6. Communication between interfaces is in real-time. API calls must not be used to send data.
For example, when the race mode is changed by the Safety Official, the flag displays change in real time.

- tehtud alljärgnevad muudatused
Front Desk (public/js/front-desk.js):

createRace() → socket.emit('create-race', { name })
deleteRace() → socket.emit('delete-race', { raceId })
addDriverToRace() → socket.emit('add-driver', { raceId, name, carNumber })
saveDriverEdit() → socket.emit('edit-driver', { raceId, entryId, name, carNumber })
removeDriver() → socket.emit('remove-driver', { raceId, entryId })
loadRaces() → socket.emit('get-races') või kasutada race-update event'e

Race Control (public/js/race-control.js):

startRace() → socket.emit('start-race', { raceId })
finishRace() → socket.emit('finish-race', { raceId })
endRaceSession() → socket.emit('end-race-session', { raceId })
setMode() → socket.emit('set-mode', { raceId, mode })
loadNextRace() → kasutada next-race Socket.IO event'i (juba olemas)

Lap-line Tracker (public/js/lap-line-tracker.js):

registerLap() → socket.emit('register-lap', { raceId, carNumber })
loadRaces() → kasutada race-update event'e või socket.emit('get-available-races')


